<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Scaly stripes on the elytra are partially fragmented (Figs 11, 13), rarely the elytra are completely maculate (Fig. 12). Antennomere 3 long and slender, three times longer than antennomere 2. Basal margin of pronotum convex medially. Male genitalia as in Figs 14-15.</paragraph>
