<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Fukien and Guangxi provinces of China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
For a long time, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyphylla (Granida) jessopi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jessopi" subGenus="Granida">Polyphylla (Granida) jessopi</taxonomicName>
was known from single male only. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Keith, D" journalOrPublisher="Kogane" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" pagination="19 - 20" title="New record of Polyphylla jessopi De Wailly, 1993 from Guangxi, China (Coleoptera, Scarabaeoidea, Melolonthidae)." volume="11" year="2010">Keith (2010)</bibRefCitation>
reported three additional specimens collected in Guangxi (China) with variable elytral pattern. Except of two specimens with the same pattern as the holotype, one male has maculate elytra. Such distinct variability in elytral pattern is very unusual in Palaearctic members of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyphylla" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Polyphylla</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
